  "description": "Ant Design is Alibaba's enterprise design language; its color system is fully algorithmic — 13 base hues each expanded into a 10-step palette by a documented generation tool, shipped precomputed in @ant-design/colors.",
  "philosophy": "Each palette is generated from a single seed color (step 6) by an HSV-based algorithm that rotates hue and adjusts saturation/value outward: steps 1-5 get lighter, steps 7-10 get darker. The 10 steps carry fixed semantics via map tokens: 1 = light background, 2 = background hover, 3 = border, 4 = border hover, 5 = hover, 6 = the primary/solid color, 7 = active/pressed, with text tokens drawn from steps 5-7. Dark mode is not a palette flip: @ant-design/colors ships genuinely separate precomputed dark palettes (presetDarkPalettes) regenerated for dark backgrounds, so dark step N is a different color, not light step (11-N). Actual UI neutrals (text, separators) additionally use alpha-based blacks/whites for blending.",
