  "notes": "roleMapping follows Ant's documented map-token derivation (colorBg=1, colorBgHover=2, colorBorder=3, colorBorderHover=4, colorHover=5, primary=6, colorActive=7, colorText=6, in 1-based steps); note solidHover (step 5) is LIGHTER than solid and active (step 7) is darker — that is genuinely Ant's convention. appBg, uiBgActive, borderSubtle and textSubtle are null because Ant fills those roles with dedicated non-palette tokens: layout background #f5f5f5/#000000, alpha fills, separator #0505050F/#FDFDFD1F, and alpha text colors #000000E0/#000000A6 (dark #FFFFFFD9/#FFFFFFA6). Gotchas: the grey preset is unusual — it starts at #a6a6a6 (no light background steps) and its last two light steps are both #000000; the docs also show a 13-step alpha-friendly neutral gray not representable in this 10-step format. The colorError seed token is #ff4d4f (red step 5, index 4), not the red preset primary #f5222d (step 6). colorWarning is the gold palette (#faad14), not yellow. colorInfo shares blue with colorPrimary. Neutral scale is the documented 13-step Neutral Color Palette (gray-1..13) from ant.design/docs/spec/colors, not the generated grey preset; Ant ships no mirrored dark neutral ramp (dark UI uses alpha text over #141414), so its dark values are null. Neutral role mapping follows the v5 tokens (colorBgLayout #f5f5f5, colorBorderSecondary #f0f0f0, colorBorder #d9d9d9, secondary text ~#595959, primary text rgba(0,0,0,.88) ~ #1f1f1f)."
